result.execSummary:
The defendant Charles James Pickle was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manufacture/Deliver THC (<=200g), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(h)1.
  • Possess w/Intent-THC (<=200 grams), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(h)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Waiver of Preliminary Hearing, Plea and Sentencing on 4/7/16
Reporter:  Karen Blair

Defendant enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Counts 1 & 2.  Count 3 to be dismissed and read-in.

Atty Hendee waives the PSI.
Atty Frank agrees and waives the PSI.
BY THE COURT:  PSI will not be ordered based on waiver of both counsel.

Atty Hendee makes sentencing recommendations.
Atty Frank makes sentencing arguments.

BY THE COURT:  Amended Ct. 1:  Court orders 3 1/2 years in the Wisconsin State Prison System with 1 1/2 years Initial Confinement and 2 years Extended Supervision with conditions; consecutive to any other sentence:
Credit = 127 days
*Court Costs = $268.00
*DNA Sample + $250.00 Surcharge
*AODA and any follow-up treatment
*Comply with & complete any and all counseling &Treatment recommended by the Agent
*Absolute Sobriety; zero tolerance
*Eligible for Challange Incarceration Program
*Eligible for Substance Abuse Program

Amended Ct. 2:  Withhold Sentence; 24 months Probation with conditions; consecutive to Ct. 1 sentence
Court Costs = $268.00
Comply with any counseling or treatment recommended by the Agent
DNA Surcharge = $250.00

  **Court advises defendant that they have been convicted of a Felony and advises rights of voting privileges and of owning a firearm.
Ct. 3 to be dismissed and read-in.

Atty Hendee states that in speaking with Atty Frank; the defendant will be waiving the Prelim today.  Atty Frank agrees and has discussed the waiver with his client.  Court questions the defendant.  Defendant agrees with the waiver.  Court accepts the waiver of the Prelim.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and this defendant committed it.  Case bound over for trial or further proceedings.

Atty Hendee files the amended information with the Court in which counts 1 & 2 have been amended to remove the enhancers.  Atty Frank states that the Defendant received a copy of the information and waives its reading.

Defendant Charles James Pickle in court with attorney Ryan T. Frank.  Defendant Charles James Pickle in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that there has been discussions on possible settlement.  Atty Hendee states that in speaking with Atty Frank, it is the defendant's wishes to move forward with a plea/sentencing today and will be waiving the Preliminary Hearing.    Atty Hendee states plea agreement to the amended Counts 1 & 2 which remove the enhancers.  Ct. 3 to be dismissed and read-in.  Atty Frank agrees.

Defendant Charles James Pickle in court with attorney Ryan T. Frank.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Frank states that parties are close to resolution and asks for a reset.

BY THE COURT:  Reset
bond continued.  Return date scheduled for April 7, 2016 at 01:45 pm.
